{
  "texts": [
    "Model PerformanceLLMs demonstrate superior performance, particularly when employing techniques such as zero-shot and few-shot learning.",
    "Both the EconMistral model (Mistral AI with a LoRA adapter) and the standard Mistral AI model (version 0.2-Instruct) achieve comparable performance gains with zero-shot prompts, indicating that the LoRA adapter does not provide significant advantages in this context.",
    "While few-shot prompts yield improvements in relevance labeling, their impact on downstream label prediction is limited.Small language models demonstrate high accuracy in relevance labeling but struggle with downstream label prediction.",
    "This weakness likely stems from the limited number of LLMs Compared LLM Performance and Prompt EngineeringThe performance of large language models varies depending on the specific engine employed.",
    "Notably, the Llama3.1 engine exhibits lower accuracy compared to the Mistral AI engine, potentially attributable to differences in their training and retrieval techniques."
  ]
}